
@startuml
skinparam linetype zigzag

class EBike {
  -frame: Frame
  -driveSystem: DriveSystem
  -controller: Controller
  -battery: Battery?
}

class Frame {
  -material: String = "steel"
}

class DriveSystem {
  -motor: Motor
}

class Motor {
  // No specific attributes or methods mentioned
}

class Battery {
  -storedEnergy: Double (Wh)
}

class Controller {
  -state: String (On, Off, Charging)
  +controlBattery()
  +commandDriveSystem()
}

class BasicController {
  // Inherits from Controller
}

class AdvancedController {
  -nextInspectionDate: Date
  +estimateNextInspectionDate(): Date
}

Controller <|-- BasicController
Controller <|-- AdvancedController

EBike "1" *-- "2" Frame
EBike "1" *-- "1" DriveSystem
EBike "1" *-- "1" Controller
EBike "1" *-- "1" Battery

DriveSystem "1" *-- "1" Motor
@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- `EBike` contains one `Frame`, one `DriveSystem`, one `Controller`, and optionally one `Battery`.
- `Frame` has a material attribute set to `"steel"`.
- `DriveSystem` consists of one `Motor`.
- `Battery` stores energy in Watt-hours.
- `Controller` has three possible states: `On`, `Off`, `Charging`.
- `Controller` controls the battery and commands the drive system.
- There are two types of controllers: `BasicController` and `AdvancedController`, both inheriting from `Controller`.
- The `AdvancedController` has an additional attribute `nextInspectionDate` and a method `estimateNextInspectionDate()`.

